        "body":  "Closeout note (post-PR #99 merge):\n\nThis dispatch executed correctly. The Claude executor reached one of the declared halt conditions in the task brief (Q4 reveals no reachable cache consumer + Q5 would require inventing image-cache product semantics → design work, not autonomous follow-up) and emitted a clean halt:\n\n```\nHANDOFF_STATUS: BLOCKED\nNEXT_ROLE: PLANNER_AI\nEXIT_CODE: 0\n```\n\nThe pre-fix `Invoke-AiDispatchQueue.ps1` only inspected the non-zero loop exit code and mis-classified the halt as a retryable failure, which is why this issue was originally labelled `ai-dispatch-failed`. The queue runner has since been fixed (`136b800`) to read the EXEC packet\u0027s `EXEC_STATUS` marker and treat `blocked` as terminal human-review work — see `AI_DISPATCH_AUTOMATION.md` §14.10.\n\nSubstantive audit content landed on `main` via PR #99 / `012f119`. Labels now reflect the actual outcome:\n- `ai-auto` (autonomous dispatch audit trail — kept)\n- `ai-dispatch-done` (positive-salvage: substantive deliverable landed)\n- `ai-dispatch-failed` (removed — the executor did not actually fail)\n\nAudit conclusion: no bounded io-image asset-store adapter dispatch is justified by current code evidence. Either possible follow-up (stub deletion vs. content-addressed identity design on `Image`) is Planner/human work, not autonomous.",
